<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="19" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d19fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                                    Attaché, London, via Navy channels at 4:05 p.m.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-02">May 2,
                                    1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>To the <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss> from the
                                President personal and secret No. 275.</p>
                            <p>I am really delighted you are coming. I agree most heartily that we
                                have some important business to settle at once; the sooner the
                                better. Marshall and King have postponed their Pacific trip. I want
                                you of course to stay here with me.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>